name: A Cutie Mouse and its Pupil
description:
A recreation of a painting made by 18th century french painter Marie-Victoire Lemoine (1754-1820) that is titled "The Interior of an Atelier of a Woman Painter" (1789). During the creation of the painting, Lemoine wasn't able to submit her artwork to the famous art exhibition The Salon of Académie Royale in Paris due to access limitations that the establishment had for women artists, though in later years she was finally able to show her works in the same exhibition in year 1796.
